<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    lang="en"
    xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
    xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
    tal:omit-tag=""
    tal:define="bodyclass string:text">

<tal:wrapper metal:use-macro="main.macros['master']">
<head>
  <title></title>
</head>
<body>
  <metal:content fill-slot="inside-header">
    <h2>Your privacy</h2>
  </metal:content>
  <metal:content fill-slot="content">
    <h3>Information we collect and how we us it</h3>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cookies</strong> &#8212; When you use mappp.me, we send one
          or more
          <dfn><a href="http://www.google.com/intl/en/privacy/faq.html#toc-terms-cookie">cookies</a></dfn>
          to your computer or other device. We use cookies to store
          identifiers of any mappps you have created which are still valid and
          your preferences for map image zoom level.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Log information</strong> &#8212; When you visit mappp.me,
          via a browser, application or other client our servers automatically
          record certain information. These
          <dfn><a href="http://www.google.com/intl/en/privacy/faq.html#toc-terms-server-logs">server logs</a></dfn>
          may include information such as your web request, your interaction
          with a service, Internet Protocol address, browser type, browser
          language, the date and time of your request and one or more cookies
          that may uniquely identify your browser.
      </li>
      <li><strong>User communications</strong> &#8212; When you send email or
          other communications to mappp.me, we may retain those communications
          in order to process your inquiries, respond to your requests and
          improve our services.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Location data</strong> &#8212; If you use mappp.me, we may
          receive information about your actual location (such as GPS signals
          sent by a mobile device) or information that can be used to
          approximate a location (such as a cell ID).

          <p>This information is stored for up to 30 minutes. You may choose
             to delete this data at
             any time be choosing 'Delete' from the administration page of your
             mappp.
          </p>
          <p>Any location you provide to us is freely accessible to the
             public, though no personally identifiable information is provided
             with it. This means that anyone might access the location whether
             you send them a link to it or not. This is a feature of this
             service and the location is in no way associated to you
             personally to any other user of this service.
          </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Choices</h3>
    <p>Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies, but you can reset
       your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is
       being sent. However, some mappp.me features and services may not
       function properly if your cookies are disabled.
    </p>
    <h3>Information sharing</h3>
    <p>mappp.me only shares personal information with other companies or
       individuals in the following limited circumstances:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>We have a good faith belief that access, use, preservation or
          disclosure of such information is reasonably necessary to (a)
          satisfy any applicable law, regulation, legal process or
          enforceable governmental request, or (b) detect, prevent, or
          otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>If mappp.me becomes involved in a merger, acquisition, or any form of
       sale of some or all of its assets, we will ensure the confidentiality
       of any personal information involved in such transactions and provide
       notice before personal information is transferred and becomes subject
       to a different privacy policy.
    </p>
    <h3>Information Security</h3>
    <p>We take appropriate security measures to protect against unauthorized
       access to or unauthorized alteration, disclosure or destruction of
       data. These include internal reviews of our data collection, storage
       and processing practices and security measures, including appropriate
       encryption and other measures to guard against unauthorized access to
       systems where we store personal data.
    </p>
    <h3>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>Please note that this Privacy Policy may change from time to time. We
       will not reduce your rights under this Privacy Policy without your
       explicit consent. We will post any Privacy Policy changes on this page
       and, if the changes are significant, we will provide a more prominent
       notice. We will also keep prior versions of this Privacy Policy in an
       archive for your review.
    </p>
    <h3>Our service providers</h3>
    <p>Services providers we use to bring you this website may also have
       access to the information you provide us with and have privacy policies
       of their own which apply. These are listed below.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://www.google.com/intl/en/privacy/privacy-policy.html">Google Privacy Policy</a>
    </ul>
  </metal:content>
</body>
</tal:wrapper>
</html>